# Sobelow 0.14.x baseline configuration for mlb_fan.
#
# Known-accepted findings (reviewed 2026-07-03, security agent PASS):
#
#   Config.CSP - Missing Content-Security-Policy in the browser pipeline.
#     Accepted: single-user local research tool; no cross-origin resources.
#     Recommendation: add a CSP header plug if the tool is ever exposed publicly.
#
#   DOS.StringToAtom - String.to_atom in MlbFan.Stats.Api.build_url/3 (line 45).
#     Accepted: the key is pulled from our own Endpoints registry (a finite, known
#     atom set defined at compile time) — not from user/model free-text input.
#     The atom table is bounded and stable.
#
#   XSS.Raw - Phoenix.HTML.raw/1 in MlbFanWeb.Markdown.to_safe_html/1 (line 20).
#     Accepted: intentional by design. Raw HTML is only called AFTER the full
#     sanitization pipeline: Earmark (escape: true) -> HtmlSanitizeEx.markdown_html
#     -> drop unsafe hrefs -> drop <img> tags. Tested by markdown_test.exs.
#
# Do not use `ignore:` to suppress findings globally — each new scan should surface
# any regressions. Review CI output manually if the finding count changes.
#
# To regenerate this file from CLI flags:
#   mix sobelow --router lib/mlb_fan_web/router.ex --private --save-config
[
  exit: false,
  format: "txt",
  ignore_files: [],
  ignore: [],
  out: nil,
  private: true,
  router: "lib/mlb_fan_web/router.ex",
  skip: false,
  threshold: :low,
  verbose: false,
  version: false
]
